I need to calculate several financial ratios based on the provided financial statements. Let's solve this step by step.

1. Free Cash Flow (FCF)
   FCF = Operating Cash Flow - Capital Expenditures
   Operating Cash Flow = -10,442,735.47
   Capital Expenditures = 2,479,994.53
   FCF = -10,442,735.47 - 2,479,994.53 = -12,922,730.00

2. Return on Assets (ROA)
   ROA = Net Income / Average Total Assets × 100%
   Net Income = 3,744,117.89
   Average Total Assets = (28,000,000.00 + 39,772,748.32) / 2 = 33,886,374.16
   ROA = (3,744,117.89 / 33,886,374.16) × 100% = 11.05%

3. Return on Equity (ROE)
   ROE = Net Income / Average Shareholders' Equity × 100%
   Net Income = 3,744,117.89
   Average Shareholders' Equity = (28,000,000.00 + 31,744,117.89) / 2 = 29,872,058.95
   ROE = (3,744,117.89 / 29,872,058.95) × 100% = 12.53%

4. Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio
   Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Net Income
   Operating Cash Flow = -10,442,735.47
   Net Income = 3,744,117.89
   Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = -10,442,735.47 / 3,744,117.89 = -2.79

5. Net Profit Margin
   Net Profit Margin = Net Income / Total Revenue × 100%
   Net Income = 3,744,117.89
   Total Revenue = 28,572,608.70
   Net Profit Margin = (3,744,117.89 / 28,572,608.70) × 100% = 13.10%

6. Gross Profit Margin
   Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue × 100%
   Gross Profit = 8,372,608.70
   Total Revenue = 28,572,608.70
   Gross Profit Margin = (8,372,608.70 / 28,572,608.70) × 100% = 29.30%
